            <h3 data-uuid="ad932fb813d7440d9e1a311bbe250198">Part 2: Write an Argument</h3>
            <h6 data-uuid="49707f8136914b7b8b8b45ba38416da3">Historical Context</h6>
            <p data-uuid="7840e6b86af045f3aa74dee830b1a5fe">In the late 1700s and early 1800s, the Industrial
                Revolution changed the way goods were produced in the United States. After the
                War of 1812 manufacturing grew more quickly. New factories were built that
                changed how many Americans lived and worked. Workers organized to ensure fair
                pay and working conditions. New technology and inventions changed the way
                people traveled, communicated, and did housework.</p>
            <h6 data-uuid="678e2f64aeff4458809caa94a6e2510f">Task</h6>
            <p data-uuid="67a4c5b83f8c465a81197cebebf93786">
                The Industrial Revolution transformed peopleâ€™s
                lives in the northern United States. It changed the way people lived and worked
                for the better and sometimes for the worse. Did the pros of the Industrial Revolution outweigh the cons? Write an argumentative essay in which you take a stand on the effects that rapid
                industrialization had on life in the North.</p>
            <p data-uuid="232bb14aeb6b4ff7857ec0ceaba14d00">Complete the following steps as you plan and compose your essay.</p>
            <ol data-uuid="2ffe2122ee3d47cb80c62d4e4d16abf7">
                <li data-uuid="281173a954d64eb5a9d517e42c9179e5">
                    Review your notes and sources before you start writing.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="78936934d708489b858ac96a9d52f6d4">
                    Use at least <i>three</i> of the sources in Part 1, and develop the topic
                    with relevant, well-chosen text evidence from the documents.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="bf6eb7b177bc4845b464ed592b61467a">
                    Clearly state your claim, or position on the topic, and consider any opposing claims.</li>
                <li data-uuid="a5ad4b33961749b9b6b275e869c2aac5">Support your claim with logical reasoning and evidence from credible sources.</li>
                <li data-uuid="0382b64e15ee46b7a09583abaf993314">Organize your essay in a clear and logical way and use linking words and phrases to clarify the relationship between claims and counterclaims, as well as between ideas.</li>
                <li data-uuid="ac1e178c919947b8929465b951375072">Use a formal writing style and correct grammar and punctuation.</li>
                <li data-uuid="a137b2c88eb546a986f6f0f2f15827e3">Write a conclusion that sums up your ideas and supports the argument you present.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
